nd visions of world order; as the newly-independent African and Asian states sought to redress the inequalities created by colonialism, the US and UK sought to maintain the status quo, while the Secretary-General Dag Hammarskjöld tried to reconcile these two contrasting views.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aDecolonizationzCongo (Democratic Republic)xHistoryy20th century. 4aInternational Relations 2019. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / Diplomacy.2bisacsh  aAfro-Asian bloc.  aAnglo-American relationship.  aCold War.  aCongolese army.  aOperation UNOKAT.  aUN Congo policy.  aUnited Nations activities in the Congo.  aconflict.  aconfusion.  aconstitutional crisis.  adecolonisation.1 aO’Malley, Alanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2018 eBook-Packagez978311128277040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152611627740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526116277423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526116277/original  a978-3-11-128277-0  Manchester University Press 2018 eBook-Packageb2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles